It looks like the culprit might be [`Intl.Segmenter`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/Segmenter/Segmenter). Running 3k lines through it takes roughly 1.4 _seconds_ on my current setup.

```js
console.time();

const lines = new Array(3000).fill('abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz').join('\n');

const segmenter = new Intl.Segmenter(undefined, { granularity: 'word' }).segment(lines);

for (const segment of segmenter) {}

console.timeEnd();
```

This is by no means an accurate (or reproducible) form of measurement, but the magnitude of it is what really matters.

---

**EDIT:** A little more accurate timing, but still the same area. Done in about 1 second.

```js
const obs = new PerformanceObserver(items => {
  console.log(items.getEntries()[0].duration);

  performance.clearMarks();
});

obs.observe({type: 'measure'});

const lines = new Array(3000).fill('abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz').join('\n');

const segmenter = new Intl.Segmenter(undefined, {granularity: 'word'}).segment(lines);

performance.mark('start');

for (const segment of segmenter);

performance.mark('finish');
performance.measure('runtime', 'start', 'finish');
```

Increase that to 100k lines and it takes a whopping 15 minutes. It's safe to say that using [`Intl.Segmenter`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/Segmenter/Segmenter) is a huge bottleneck in this case.

Environment: Flutter 3.35.6 • Dart 3.9.2 • Windows 11 • Chrome 141 / Edge 142


Findings

Per-span cursor height: Not supported today. TextField exposes one global cursorHeight for the whole field; it doesn’t adapt per TextSpan.

Selection height for mixed sizes: Selection rectangles are line/paragraph based. selectionHeightStyle: BoxHeightStyle.max uses the full line box but does not expand per span.

Vertical cropping: Reproduced without a strut; resolved by adding StrutStyle sized to the largest span (code below).

import 'dart:ui' as ui;
final biggest = Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineLarge!;
TextField(
  controller: myController, // builds mixed-size TextSpans
  // Prevent vertical clipping:
  strutStyle: StrutStyle(
    forceStrutHeight: true,
    fontSize: biggest.fontSize,
    height: biggest.height ?? 1.2,
    leadingDistribution: TextLeadingDistribution.even,
  ),
  // Best available option for selection boxes (still line-based):
  selectionHeightStyle: ui.BoxHeightStyle.max,
  // Optional: choose ONE cursor height globally (no per-span support yet)
  // cursorHeight: biggest.fontSize,
  maxLines: null,
);

