Hi @angelosilvestre, thanks for reporting this issue. Is this also an issue on Android? It may be that the method we use to disable the context menu is not compatible with all platforms.

```dart
element.addEventListener('contextmenu', (DomEvent event) {
    event.preventDefault();
});
```

edit:

looks like according to the [mdn web docs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/contextmenu_event) the event is not supported on iOS with Safari.

> ```dart
> element.addEventListener('contextmenu', (DomEvent event) {
>     event.preventDefault();
> });
> ```

Is there a way to disable the default iOS toolbar in Safari? 
BrowserContextMenu.disableContextMenu(); works fine in other browsers, but I still can't find the solution for Safari (it shows the shared buttons and also the custom toolbar I added, the idea is not to show the native buttons).

