issues.body:
## Steps to Reproduce

<!-- Please include full steps to reproduce so that we can reproduce the problem. -->

1. Execute `flutter run` on the code sample <!-- (see "Code sample" section below) -->
2. Tap one of the three buttons. A dialog should open in which a text field is autofocussed, so the soft keyboard should open as well.
3.  look at the distance between the bottom edge of the dialog and the top edge of the opened keyboard: it is too large

**Expected results:** <!-- what did you want to see? -->
In the dialog that is opened by tapping the TextButton `Show dialog: content wrapped with AnimatedPadding widget` I used `MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom` as padding. The dialogs opened by the other buttons open widgets wrapped by `Dialog` or `AlertDialog` which both use `MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom` as padding too.

Documentation states `MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets` is the following:

```
  /// The parts of the display that are completely obscured by system UI,
  /// typically by the device's keyboard.
  ///
  /// When a mobile device's keyboard is visible `viewInsets.bottom`
  /// corresponds to the top of the keyboard.
```

So when using `MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom` as padding for the dialog widget, the edges of the soft keyboard and the dialog widget should touch.

**Actual results:** <!-- what did you see? -->
However, there is a large gap between the top edge of the soft keyboard and the bottom edge of the dialog widget. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/39117631/136963486-51baf32c-536e-4261-9517-875d8c5cddbd.png)


<details>
<summary>Code sample</summary>

